Interview Questions & Answers

**1. What is normalization?**
Process of organizing data to reduce redundancy and improve integrity.

**2. Primary vs Foreign Key**
Primary key uniquely identifies a record. Foreign key links one table to another.

**3. What are constraints?**
Rules applied to columns (e.g., NOT NULL, UNIQUE, PRIMARY KEY).

**4. What is a surrogate key?**
Artificial/system-generated key (like auto-increment ID).

**5. How do you avoid data redundancy?**
By using normalization and proper table relationships.

**6. What is ER diagram?**
Entity-Relationship diagram â€” visual representation of database structure.

**7. Types of relationships in DBMS?**
One-to-One, One-to-Many, Many-to-Many.

**8. Purpose of AUTO_INCREMENT?**
Automatically generates unique ID for each new record.

**9. Default storage engine in MySQL?**
InnoDB.

**10. What is a composite key?**
A key made using two or more columns to uniquely identify a record.